  m_Name: Pes_Proximal_Phalanx_D4_L
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Pes_Proximal_Phalanx_D4_L
  partName: Pes Proximal Phalanx D4 Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left proximal phalanx of the fourth hind digit is positioned between the
    metatarsal and middle phalanx within the canine hindpaw. It contributes to toe
    flexibility, balanced locomotion, and controlled movement during weight-bearing
    activities. Ligaments and tendons attached to the bone enable flexion
  - and extension of the digit while stabilizing the hindpaw during ground contact.
    The fourth digit also assists with traction and shock distribution throughout
    the limb during movement. Proper alignment and integrity of this phalanx are
    essential for smooth gait patterns and coordinated locomotion.
